goths. Clovis' victory proved a crucial step in the expulsion of the Visigoths from Francia into Spain, thereby leaving Gaul largely to the Franks. It was arguably in the wake of Vouillé that Gaul became Francia, and that "France began." The editors have united an international team of experts on Late Antiquity and the Merovingian Kingdoms to reexamine the battle from multiple as well as interdisciplinary perspectives. The contributions address questions of military strategy, geographical location, archaeological footprint, political background, religious propaganda, consequences (both in Francia and in Italy), and significance. There is a strong focus on the close reading of primary source-material, both textual and material, secular and theological.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aFrankreich. 4aGeschichte. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aHistory of France.  aLate Antiquity.  aVouillé.1 aArnold, Jonathan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachrach, Bernard S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeliyannis, Deborah Mauskopf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalfond, Gregory I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathisen, Ralph W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathisen, Ralph W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShanzer, Danuta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShanzer, Danuta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWood, Ian, econtributor.